# Downstream-differential negate (analysis sec 4.5 R9): a monotone-negated
# negate (out) feeding a differential join (flag_out : out, active). Probes
# the R3 seed-before-drain ordering: a leaked phantom `out` frontier entry
# would double-count one stratum down in flag_out.
#
# Batch 1: feed (1,10),(2,20); active 1,2. No unsee.
#          out = {(1,10),(2,20)}, flag_out = {(1,10),(2,20)}.
# Batch 2: unsee 1. `-` crossover retracts out(1,10); flag_out(1,10) must
#          also drop (out's net_removals flow downstream).
#          flag_out = {(2,20)}.
# Batch 3: active flip -active 2 / +active 3 in one epoch. active now {1,3}.
#          out unchanged = {(2,20)} (only key 2 fed); flag_out loses (2,20)
#          (active 2 gone) and gains nothing (no out for key 3).
#          flag_out = {}.
# Batch 4: feed (3,30). out gains (3,30); active 3 present -> flag_out(3,30).
#          flag_out = {(3,30)}.
batch
+ feed 1 10
+ feed 2 20
+ active 1
+ active 2
end

batch
+ unsee 1
end

batch
- active 2
+ active 3
end

batch
+ feed 3 30
end
